An Afghan man and his son look out a window at the refugee camp of Kara Tepe in the island of Lesbos, Greece on Wednesday. Last week, the Greek government announced it would shut down its three largest overcrowded migrant camps on the islands facing Turkey, and replace them with new larger facilities. Photo: AFP  
